This paper deals with the problem of evaluating multiway joins in a parallel and communication-free way, which is a common problem in distributed databases (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the complexity of parallel-correctness and its constituents, which involves logical reasoning and complexity theory (cs.DC, cs.LO). The paper also deals with the containment problem for conjunctive queries with negation, which is a well-studied problem in database theory and artificial intelligence (cs.CC, cs.AI).
